<p>Presidentsâ€™ popularity tends to wane. In his second term Donald Trumpâ€™s has fallen faster than that of his recent predecessors.</p>
<p>Since modern polling began most presidents have started their terms with positive net approval ratings (the share of voters who approve of their job performance minus the share who disapprove). Now it is -18, the lowest it has been since his inaugurationâ€”and three percentage-points lower than at any point in his first term.</p>
<p>Mr Trump has set in motion a dramatic transformation of Americaâ€™s government. Largely by executive fiat he has reshaped its trade arrangements, immigration system, workforce and foreign policy. He has also used his bully pulpit (and the Department of Justice) to attack universities, the legal profession, the press and various businesses.
